added.title: The Goons
added.description: Gumball sets out to win his Dad back by winning a blindfolded "dumb" race.

added.title: The Secret
added.description: Gumball almost loses his mind trying to guess Darwin's secret.

added.title: The Sock
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are taught confusing lessons about honesty by the school councillor.

added.title: The Genius
added.description: Darwin is sent away to a government institute for geniuses. Yes. Really.

added.title: The Poltergeist
added.description: Gumball and Darwin give Mr Robinson a home and end up saving his marriage.

added.title: The Legend of the Library
added.description: When the library is thrown into disarray, an ancient ghost is awoken.

added.title: Locked Out Cold
added.description: On the eve of a big holiday party, the Williams kids are locked out of the house, leading to a frantic search all over town for a spare key.

added.title: Beyond the Overpass
added.description: The Capture the Flag war is over. Craig returns to the Creek, hoping to get some recognition for his heroic deeds, but finds a new quest instead.

added.title: Sink or Swim Team
added.description: Craig offers to help the Sewer Queen by going undercover as a member of the swim team.

added.title: The Quick Name
added.description: Craig tries to rid himself of a bad nickname.

added.title: The Gym
added.description: The Bears go to the gym and get quite the work out.

added.title: Bubble
added.description: Panda becomes a germophobe and decides to live the rest of his life in a bubble.

added.title: Baby Orphan Ninja Bears
added.description: The Baby Bears venture into the sewers and meet a ninja-like martial arts master.

added.title: Fire!
added.description: Grizz's quick thinking prevents a potential wild fire, but the praise he receives from doing so quickly goes to his head.

added.title: Ranger Norm
added.description: When Tabes leaves for a conference, the Bears have to deal with her substitute, Ranger Norm.

added.title: Sister Sitter
added.description: When Blossom and Bubbles get sick, Buttercup volunteers to take care of them for the day.

added.title: Odd Bubbles Out
added.description: When Donny the Unicorn visits, Bubbles becomes jealous of his new friend.

added.title: Presidential Punchout
added.description: When Morbucks enters the Student Body President race, Blossom sinks to her level to secure the win.

added.title: Cheep Thrills
added.description: After finding a baby monster in the park, Bubbles insists on adopting it without considering the consequences!

added.title: Fashion Forward
added.description: When the Fashionistas launch a new line of brainwashing clothing, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop the fashion trend before it's too late.

added.title: Gem Hunt
added.description: Steven and Connie track a Gem monster through the wilderness but its tracks lead them to mystery.

added.title: Crack the Whip
added.description: Amethyst is left in charge of Steven and Connie, and there will be no training while she's around!

added.title: Steven vs. Amethyst
added.description: Steven and Amethyst get competitive while training with Pearl.

added.title: Bismuth
added.description: Steven discovers something the Gems thought was lost to the past inside of Lion's mane.

added.title: Beta
added.description: Steven and Amethyst visit some friends in the country but Amethyst isn't being herself.

added.title: Candy Streets
added.description: Lumpy Space Princess is robbed and faints before she can tell Finn and Jake who robbed her.

added.title: Wizards Only, Fools
added.description: Princess Bubblegum believes magic is nothing but a bunch of hooey. When Starchy gets sick and asks her to use magic to cure him, she asks Finn and Jake to help her sneak into Wizard City to get a cold spell.

added.title: Jakesuit
added.description: Jake is sick and tired of Finn using his body as a suit of armor so he convinces Finn to trade places to show him how much it really stinks.

added.title: Be More
added.description: Finn and Jake disguise themselves as MOs in order to infiltrate the MO factory in hopes of saving BMO from malfunctioning.

added.title: Cat Videos
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to get Benson to stop watching cat videos.

added.title: Struck by Lightning
added.description: Muscle Man and High Five Ghost get struck by lightning and can't remember each other.

added.title: The Return of Party Horse
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to help their friend Party Horse get back together with his girlfriend.

added.title: Sleep Cycle
added.description: After staying up for two straight nights watching a movie marathon, Mordecai and Rigby have to get their sleep cycle back on track.

added.title: Just Friends
added.description: Rigby and Eileen get called away to Don's black belt ceremony forcing Mordecai and Margaret to hang out alone.

added.title: Slumber Party
added.description: Clarence struggles to make a connection at an all-girls slumber party, leaving Sumo and Jeff at odds without Clarence as their "friendship buffer."

added.title: Nature Clarence
added.description: Clarence, Sumo and Jeff's nature hike veers off course courtesy of their under qualified, overwhelmed guide Josh, prompting Clarence to take the lead.

added.title: Average Jeff
added.description: Jeff suffers an identity crisis when a standardized test lands him in the lesser of the classes academic groupings.

added.title: Lizard Day Afternoon
added.description: Clarence and Sumo chase a lizard to unexpected rewards as Jeff jockeys for playing time on Belson's spectacular new gaming system.

added.title: The Forgotten
added.description: After Clarence and his indecisive classmate Brady are left behind at school, Brady is forced to tag along on Clarence's adventure home.

added.title: Tongue Tied
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a shy kid gain confidence.

added.title: Uncle Dummy
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve try to convince Mr. Gus that his ventriloquist dummy is alive.

added.title: Face Fix
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve help Mr. Gus try to get his face back to normal before an important photo shoot.

added.title: The Phone Call
added.description: A threatening phone call from a stranger causes the gang to panic.

added.title: Uncle Cupid
added.description: Cupid, too lonely to perform his Valentine's Day duties, comes to Uncle Grandpa for help.

added.title: Another Five More Short Graybles
added.description: Why are Finn and Jake building a time machine? Can Princess Bubblegum help Cinnamon Bun conquer his fear of the dark?
